The 200 fans of Barcelona who were in attendance at the Santiago Bernabeu for the Copa del Rey semi-final against Real Madrid had time to enjoy their side running riot behind enemy lines.
In watching their team run out 3-0 victors to reach another Copa del Rey final, they found time to poke fun at their rivals.With the match already finished, the Catalans had a song for Cristiano Ronaldo to twist the knife.
“Where is CR7?” was the cry from the pocket of visiting fans to mock the opposition’s lack of goals.
It didn’t sit well with the Madridistas, who attempted to silence them whistles.

